We also measured the offensiveness (OFF) of each resource, i.e., the percentage of assertions that were marked as inappropriate or offensive materials by at least one of the human-annotators. Quasimodo and StereoKG, extracted from raw social media contents, have the highest number of assertions considered offensive (18% and 13%). Meanwhile, \systemname{}'s judicious filters only miss a small fraction (1% of final assertions).